Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Graduate Regular scale.

GAME 610: Game Production. 3 credits.
Studio and lecture course in the history, practice and design and production of computer games with an emphasis on serious games development. Students will research, design and develop a fully functioning game, for desktop, console, and/or mobile platforms in this two-semester course. This course will also support the thesis research and project development.Offered by Computer Game Design. May be repeated within the degree for a maximum 6 credits.
Recommended Prerequisite: Admittance to the MA Game Design Program or permission of instructor.
Registration Restrictions: Enrollment limited to students with a class of Advanced to Candidacy, Graduate, Junior Plus, Non-Degree or Senior Plus.Enrollment is limited to Graduate, Non-Degree or Undergraduate level students.Students in a Non-Degree Undergraduate degree may not enroll.
Schedule Type: Lecture
Grading: This course is graded on the Graduate Regular scale.

